// Semantic direction:
// inkrementell_kompilering reuses cached results for unchanged source regions, reducing rebuild time.
// spørring_system is the demand-driven computation model: results are computed lazily and cached.
// spørring_nøkkel uniquely identifies a computation (e.g. "type_av_funksjon(modul::foo)").
// memoiseringslagring persists spørring results across compiler invocations to disk.
// api_hash fingerprints the public interface of a module; impl_hash fingerprints the implementation.
// minimal_rekompilering: only modules whose api_hash changed need to recompile their dependents.
// bakover_avhengighet tracks which modules depend on a given module, enabling targeted invalidation.
// leksikalsk_treffer: if only kommentarer changed, no re-tokenization is needed (structure identical).
// reparsér_region re-parses only the minimal AST subtree covering the changed token range.
// type_sjekk_spørring is the demand for the type of one expression, triggering recursive sub-queries.
// salsa_database is the incremental computation substrate (inspired by the Salsa framework).
// salsa_input is raw source data that can be updated; all derived queries depend transitively on inputs.
// salsa_durability classifies inputs: high durability (stdlib) is rarely invalidated.
// salsa_revision is a monotone counter incremented on every input change for cache validity.
// salsa_fork creates an isolated view of the database for speculative compilation.
// arbeid_stjeling lets idle arbeidstaker threads steal kompilerings_enheter from busy ones.

// Primitive flow:
// bruker endrer funksjon foo() i modul A:
//   fil_fingeravtrykk_ik(A) endret -> invalidér alle spørringer på A
//   api_hash(A) uendret? -> kun invalidér impl-avhengige spørringer
//   api_hash(A) endret? -> bakover_avhengighet -> invalidér B, C som importerer A
// type_sjekk_spørring("type_av(foo.kall)"): sjekk salsa_cache
//   cache treff (salsa_revision uendret): returner lagret type
//   cache bom: kjør type_inferens -> lagre resultat + avhengigheter
// parallell: bygg arbeidskø av alle invalide kompilerings_enheter
//   arbeidstaker_pool(N) -> distribuer enheter -> arbeid_stjeling ved ubalanse
//   parallell_type_sjekk: uavhengige moduler sjekkes samtidig

// This defines incremental compilation: demand-driven query system with memoization, API vs impl
// hashing for minimal invalidation, lexical/syntactic/semantic incrementality, Salsa-architecture
// database, and parallel compilation with work stealing.
